{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"935b1816-5928-417d-a5bb-36790092a7bc","content":"No workflow files found in the current directory. I'll give you general guidance for the switch:\n\n### Switching to NuGet Trusted Publishing (OIDC)\n\n**1. On nuget.org** — configure a Trusted Publisher for your package:\n- Go to your package → **Manage** → **Trusted publishers**\n- Add a GitHub Actions publisher (owner, repo, optional workflow/environment)\n\n**2. In your workflow** — make these changes:\n\n```yaml\n# ADD these permissions at the job level\njobs:\n  publish:\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write   # Required for OIDC token request\n      contents: read\n\n    steps:\n      # REMOVE the old push step using API key:\n      # - run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }} ...\n\n      # REPLACE with trusted publishing:\n      - name: Push to NuGet\n        run: |\n          dotnet nuget add source \"https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\" \\\n            --name nuget.org \\\n            --username \"az\" \\\n            --password \"${{ steps.oidc.outputs.id-token }}\" \\\n            --store-password-in-clear-text\n          dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --source nuget.org\n```\n\n**Or, more commonly**, use the official **NuGet push with `--api-key`** replaced by the OIDC token flow:\n\n```yaml\n      - name: Install .NET 9+ SDK\n        uses: actions/setup-dotnet@v4\n\n      - name: Publish NuGet package\n        run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg\n              --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\nWith trusted publishers configured on nuget.org and `id-token: write` set, `dotnet nuget push` authenticates automatically via the GitHub OIDC token — **no API key needed**.\n\n**3. Clean up** — remove the `NUGET_API_KEY` secret from your repo settings once verified.\n\n### Key takeaways\n| Before | After |\n|---|---|\n| `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` | OIDC token (automatic) |\n| No special permissions | `id-token: write` required |\n| No nuget.org config | Trusted publisher configured |\n\nWould you like me to modify a specific workflow file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bf23eea0-6acc-40ab-ac8a-c7b50ddab245","outputTokens":579,"requestId":"E430:147A9A:6BDB06C:742C036:6A03CCCA"},"id":"d2f5ed4e-c2fd-4885-b8f7-feb0c08cb732","timestamp":"2026-05-13T00:59:03.606Z","parentId":"11566d8e-e706-4328-89f9-0c8a0610440e"}
